# Merge strategy for the repo's append-only prose + structured tracking files.
#
# NONE of these use `merge=union` anymore. Union merge takes all lines from all branches, which
# looked safe for "prose that only ever grows" (CHANGELOG entries, per-doc changelog footers) — but
# across a SQUASH-divergent or cross-branch promotion (e.g. dev → integration → main, where main's
# history is rewritten by squash-landing) it silently appends BOTH sides of a touched block, producing
# DUPLICATE entries: duplicate CHANGELOG headings (markdownlint MD024) and duplicate ADR/RFC changelog
# bullets. Those are syntactically valid but semantically broken, and they slip through unless caught
# by a lint gate (CLAUDE.md swarm mitigation #2 — originally applied to idmap.tsv / issues.yaml; now
# extended to the prose files for the same reason).
#
# All of these therefore use the default 3-way merge: a genuine collision surfaces as an EXPLICIT
# conflict to reconcile by hand — never a silent duplicate (G2). These files are append-only by
# discipline (new entry at the top / a new dated bullet), so real conflicts are rare and, when they
# happen, are exactly what a human should see.
#
#   CHANGELOG.md, docs/notes/*.md, docs/rfcs/*.md, docs/adr/*.md  — default 3-way merge (was union)
#   tools/github/idmap.tsv, tools/github/issues.yaml             — default 3-way merge (since #397)
#
# (Intentionally no `merge=union` lines here. Do not re-add them without a decision — they trade a
# rare explicit conflict for a silent, lint-only-detectable duplicate.)
